Conditional rendering basically means showcasing some portion or the entire portion of the UI based on some conditions,
 There are 4 ways to actually achieve Conditional Rendering in React : 

 (i) if/else
 (ii)Element variables
 (iii)Ternary Conditional Operator
 (iv) Short Circuit Operator

this.state { 
   isLoggedIn : true 
  }


(i) If/ELSE approach :  if(isLoggedIn){
   return <div>Welcome Arya </div>
   }
else{
  return <div>Welcome Guest</div>
  }

(ii) Element variables : 

  Element variables means : these are just javascript variables that will contain the elements 

  let messsgae 

  if(isLoggedIn){
    message = <div> Welcome Arya </div>
    }
 else  {

   message = <div> Welcome Guest </div>
   }
return message


Note :  We cannot use the above two approches inside the jsx.

 (iii) Ternary Conditional Operator 

 But we can use this approach inside the jsx


    return (
       this.state.isLoggedIn ? 
      <div> Welcome Vishwas </div> : 
      <div> Welcome Guest </div>


    (iv)  Short - circuit operator approach 
       : It is just a special case of the ternary Conditional Operator 

        This approach is used when we want something to render or render nothing at all .


           this.length.isLoggedIn && <div>Welcome Vishwas </div>
      
   


   
